WEBVTT

1
00:01:07.359 --> 00:01:08.443
[gasps]

2
00:01:20.622 --> 00:01:22.749
Hey. Mom. came as fast as I could.

3
00:01:24.001 --> 00:01:25.002
Show me.

4
00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:34.094
You didn't see anybody?

5
00:01:34.178 --> 00:01:35.179
No.

6
00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:41.977
Why would someone break into
Dad's office?

7
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:44.354
I don't know.

8
00:01:44.855 --> 00:01:47.941
- Anything missing?
- No. Not that I can tell.

9
00:01:49.401 --> 00:01:50.485
I overreacted.

10
00:01:50.944 --> 00:01:52.362
I shouldn't have called you.

11
00:01:52.863 --> 00:01:56.408
Sheriff said there'd been break-ins
in the area. probably just kids.

12
00:01:59.703 --> 00:02:02.039
Dad always had a place
for everything. didn't he?

13
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:06.752
Well. that's one way of putting it.

14
00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:15.177
First time I beat them to the top.

15
00:02:15.844 --> 00:02:18.680
- You were so proud.
- I was positive they let me win.

16
00:02:19.765 --> 00:02:20.933
Used to drive me crazy.

17
00:02:27.022 --> 00:02:28.190
You should get cameras.

18
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:30.734
And be spied on? No. thank you.

19
00:02:33.654 --> 00:02:34.821
No need for it. Really.

20
00:02:36.031 --> 00:02:38.200
- I'm sorry I bothered you.
- No problem.

21
00:02:39.326 --> 00:02:40.494
I'm glad I was nearby.

22
00:02:40.619 --> 00:02:42.162
[phone vibrates]

23
00:02:43.956 --> 00:02:45.332
Aren't you gonna take that?

24
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:47.626
It's probably just work.

25
00:02:48.919 --> 00:02:50.629
- Teddi.
- Take it.

26
00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:52.339
Hey. Teddi.

27
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:54.341
How do you feel about
a nice drive to Montana?

28
00:02:54.675 --> 00:02:55.717
Montana?

29
00:02:55.801 --> 00:02:56.927
Go.

30
00:02:58.262 --> 00:02:59.346
Yeah.

31
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:02.266
Why don't I call you tomorrow
morning to get the details?

32
00:03:02.349 --> 00:03:03.350
Thanks.

33
00:03:04.518 --> 00:03:06.436
I'm fine. You can go now.

34
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:08.480
No. I'd feel better
if I spent the night.

35
00:03:19.658 --> 00:03:24.580
So $35.000 is offered for information
as to the whereabouts of Jackson Cheong.

36
00:03:24.663 --> 00:03:29.126
{\an8}<i>age 27. works as an accountant</i>
<i>in Missoula. Montana.</i>

37
00:03:29.209 --> 00:03:32.254
{\an8}<i>The reward was posted by his parents.</i>
<i>Mark and Eden.</i>

38
00:03:43.182 --> 00:03:44.892
It's a recent photo of your son Jackson?

39
00:03:45.017 --> 00:03:48.353
About a year ago.
He was volunteering at the library.

40
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:49.521
Free tax advice.

41
00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:51.481
[woman] Jackson was a bit shy.

42
00:03:51.565 --> 00:03:54.359
so it was good for him to get out
and meet people.

43
00:03:54.443 --> 00:03:57.154
- You said he met a woman?
- Yeah. Rebecca Smith.

44
00:03:57.237 --> 00:03:58.447
How long ago was that?

45
00:03:58.530 --> 00:04:01.366
- About two months ago.
- You have a photo of her?

46
00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:07.998
You can say it...

47
00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:12.294
She's too old for him.
Twenty years at least.

48
00:04:12.961 --> 00:04:14.838
Your son's 27 years old.
He's an adult.

49
00:04:15.589 --> 00:04:16.882
If you're looking for someone

50
00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:19.301
to tell him who not to
fall in love with. that's not me.

51
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:21.470
It's not that. He's missing.

52
00:04:22.012 --> 00:04:24.389
Quit his job.
canceled his cell phones.

53
00:04:24.473 --> 00:04:27.601
left his apartment
and emptied his bank accounts.

54
00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:29.186
You think something happened to him?

55
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.522
Hopefully it's nothing
and we're just overreacting.

56
00:04:31.605 --> 00:04:32.606
He's our only child.

57
00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:34.024
[speaking other language]

58
00:04:34.107 --> 00:04:38.237
We tried to track down Rebecca Smith
ourselves. but there's nothing online.

59
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:39.988
We can't figure out where she works.

60
00:04:40.072 --> 00:04:41.907
What makes you so sure
he's with her now?

61
00:04:41.990 --> 00:04:43.951
He was with her
the last time we spoke to him.

62
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:47.162
I don't know how to say it.
he's taken with her. I guess.

63
00:04:47.246 --> 00:04:50.332
The moment Jackson met that woman.
he changed.

64
00:04:50.415 --> 00:04:53.544
Stopped returning our calls.
missing family dinners.

65
00:04:53.627 --> 00:04:55.337
And his accounting firm called.

66
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.298
looking for him
after he missed a few client's meetings.

67
00:04:58.924 --> 00:05:02.219
And then two weeks later.
he quit his job and vanished.

68
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.096
Anything else you can recall?

69
00:05:04.179 --> 00:05:06.849
The last time we saw him.
he looked tired.

70
00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:09.226
like he's been up for days.

71
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:11.979
He said he was doing
some work for Rebecca.

72
00:05:12.062 --> 00:05:14.481
When I asked him what it was.
he said it was the kind

73
00:05:14.565 --> 00:05:17.985
that people can't find out about.
that he could get in trouble for it.

74
00:05:18.068 --> 00:05:19.486
Any idea what that might be?

75
00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:21.905
I'm thinking this Rebecca
has him cooking books

76
00:05:21.989 --> 00:05:24.741
or laundering money.
and he wasn't himself.

77
00:05:24.825 --> 00:05:26.743
Something bad has happened to him.

78
00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:28.453
I just know it.

79
00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:31.832
[phone vibrating]

80
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:36.837
Bobby.

81
00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:39.089
Rebecca Smith? "Smith"?
Are you kidding me?

82
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:40.841
There's a million results.

83
00:05:40.924 --> 00:05:42.259
Oh. good. You got my text.

84
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:43.760
You're lucky I speak Colter.

85
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:47.347
Most people wouldn't know what to do
with a random photo. zero context.

86
00:05:47.431 --> 00:05:49.683
<i>next to one of the most
common names in North America.</i>

87
00:05:49.766 --> 00:05:51.435
Is this when
you tell me how hard it was

88
00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:52.769
but you managed to find her?

89
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.314
Pretty much.
But I don't have her yet.

90
00:05:55.397 --> 00:05:57.399
How long will it take
to sift through all that?

91
00:05:57.482 --> 00:06:00.360
No time at all. There's an app for that.
Built it myself.

92
00:06:00.444 --> 00:06:01.486
Of course you did.

93
00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:04.489
Okay. Good news and bad news.

94
00:06:04.573 --> 00:06:07.910
No matches for the facial recognition
overlap the name.

95
00:06:07.993 --> 00:06:11.622
{\an8}but I do have a mugshot
for a Rebecca Pendergast.

96
00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:13.373
who's looking real. same same.

97
00:06:13.457 --> 00:06:14.833
"Same" like identical?

98
00:06:14.917 --> 00:06:15.918
See for yourself.

99
00:06:21.715 --> 00:06:24.468
Yeah. that's her.
So she's using a fake name.

100
00:06:25.636 --> 00:06:27.513
Mugshot? What was she in for?

101
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:31.225
"Insurance fraud. wire fraud.
plus some tax evasion."

102
00:06:31.308 --> 00:06:33.810
But she hasn't served any time.
The charges were dropped.

103
00:06:33.894 --> 00:06:36.271
Jackson's parents said
his of bank accounts were drained.

104
00:06:36.355 --> 00:06:38.607
Sounds like she's a con woman
and he's the next mark.

105
00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:41.818
- You said insurance fraud. any chance...
- Great minds.

106
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:50.827
Yep. cross-referenced with
Jackson Cheong. and there's our girl.

107
00:06:50.953 --> 00:06:55.499
Ooh! She's the beneficiary of
a big old fat policy Jackson took out.

108
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:57.543
That application have an address on it?

109
00:07:58.896 --> 00:08:02.399
[man speaking indistinctly]

110
00:08:07.446 --> 00:08:08.739
[man] <i>Make it stop!</i>

111
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:10.532
<i>She's trying to kill me!</i>

112
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:15.370
<i>- No. I don't want you!</i>
- [woman] <i>That's fine.</i>

113
00:08:15.454 --> 00:08:17.539
<i>But I have to ask...</i>
[continues indistinctly]

114
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:20.417
- [man on video] <i>You can't make me!</i>
- What the hell?

115
00:08:24.129 --> 00:08:27.716
[man] <i>How do you know?</i>
<i>You don't know anything about me!</i>

116
00:08:27.841 --> 00:08:30.969
- [voices chattering on video]
- [man] <i>Why is this happening to me?</i>

117
00:08:31.053 --> 00:08:33.096
<i>It's not fair!</i>

118
00:08:33.514 --> 00:08:36.600
{\an8}<i>You can't make me!</i>
<i>How do you know?</i>

119
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:38.769
{\an8}<i>You don't know anything about me.</i>

120
00:08:41.146 --> 00:08:43.774
{\an8}<i>What is happening? It's not fair.</i>

121
00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:55.202
[voices chattering indistinctly
over video]

122
00:08:57.246 --> 00:08:58.372
[vehicle approaching]

123
00:09:06.630 --> 00:09:07.714
Who the hell are you?

124
00:09:07.798 --> 00:09:11.468
Yeah. sorry I kicked the door in.
It's a bit of a misunderstanding.

125
00:09:11.552 --> 00:09:14.304
It's actually a funny story.
if you care to hear it. Guess not.

126
00:09:14.596 --> 00:09:16.723
[all grunting]

127
00:09:20.894 --> 00:09:23.021
[grunting]

128
00:09:32.990 --> 00:09:34.324
Let's try this again.

129
00:09:34.992 --> 00:09:36.076
Who the hell are you?

130
00:09:36.869 --> 00:09:37.870
Colter Shaw.

131
00:09:38.328 --> 00:09:39.454
Let me see some ID.

132
00:09:40.163 --> 00:09:41.164
Pocket.

133
00:09:43.792 --> 00:09:46.169
Like I said. man.
I don't want any trouble. okay?

134
00:09:46.253 --> 00:09:47.754
I'm not here to steal things.

135
00:09:47.838 --> 00:09:49.756
I'm here on a job. just like you guys.

136
00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:51.967
What "job" is that?

137
00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:53.802
I'm looking for Jackson Cheong.

138
00:09:56.388 --> 00:09:59.183
Never heard of him.
This is private property.

139
00:09:59.266 --> 00:10:01.852
We can call the cops and have you
arrested for break-in.

140
00:10:01.935 --> 00:10:05.105
Maybe I'll shoot you.
Tell them I was standing my ground.

141
00:10:05.189 --> 00:10:07.608
If you were gonna shoot me.
you would've done it already.

142
00:10:07.691 --> 00:10:09.109
Same goes for calling the cops.

143
00:10:10.819 --> 00:10:12.988
I'm just gonna go. all right?
Don't want any trouble.

144
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:19.786
Better not see you here again.

145
00:10:19.870 --> 00:10:20.913
Yeah.

146
00:10:23.749 --> 00:10:25.375
[Colter] <i>Got a bad feeling about this.</i>

147
00:10:25.459 --> 00:10:28.629
- What are you talking about?
<i>- Rebecca Pendergast.</i>

148
00:10:28.712 --> 00:10:30.923
She's got an impressive
surveillance setup.

149
00:10:31.006 --> 00:10:32.007
Private security.

150
00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.259
<i>Whatever Jackson Cheong's
got himself involved in.</i>

151
00:10:34.343 --> 00:10:37.054
- it's much worse than a bad romance.
<i>- You're thinking blackmail?</i>

152
00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:40.349
- Some kind of kidnapping ring?
<i>- I don't know yet.</i>

153
00:10:43.352 --> 00:10:45.312
I'm gonna find out
what the hell's going on.

154
00:11:19.555 --> 00:11:22.516
[woman] A potential transformation.
it's there.

155
00:11:22.808 --> 00:11:25.978
The part of you
that is ready to change.

156
00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:29.940
Put aside all those negative thoughts
standing in your way.

157
00:11:30.774 --> 00:11:32.818
All those walls you let others put up.

158
00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:36.947
Walls so high. they block the light
that shines for us all.

159
00:11:39.491 --> 00:11:41.076
Are you ready to see the light?

160
00:11:41.159 --> 00:11:42.411
[all] We're ready.

161
00:11:43.287 --> 00:11:45.581
One man can lead you to it.

162
00:11:46.582 --> 00:11:47.666
Seth.

163
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:49.126
[applauding]

164
00:11:57.676 --> 00:11:58.719
[Seth] Close your eyes.

165
00:12:00.095 --> 00:12:02.681
We must see the light
before we can feel it.

166
00:12:03.223 --> 00:12:04.266
[all] We see it.

167
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:08.228
It's here for you. It's all around us.

168
00:12:08.312 --> 00:12:12.566
waiting to be tapped by those
who are willing to put in the work.

169
00:12:14.401 --> 00:12:15.903
[whispering indistinctly]

170
00:12:23.368 --> 00:12:24.411
You. sir.

171
00:12:25.162 --> 00:12:28.749
I see you.
I see what you're carrying.

172
00:12:30.167 --> 00:12:32.711
The pain like a stone.

173
00:12:35.297 --> 00:12:36.715
Colter. is it?

174
00:12:37.925 --> 00:12:39.301
Colter Shaw.

175
00:12:41.178 --> 00:12:42.596
We have much to discuss.

176
00:12:43.847 --> 00:12:45.766
I look forward to our time together.

177
00:12:49.895 --> 00:12:50.979
And you. ma'am.

178
00:12:52.648 --> 00:12:53.774
I see your loss.

179
00:12:55.526 --> 00:12:57.653
I see the grief
that you're trying to hide.

180
00:13:17.049 --> 00:13:19.135
So. it's a cult.

181
00:13:20.553 --> 00:13:24.390
I don't think they'd use that word.
but. yes. they're offering empowerment.

182
00:13:24.473 --> 00:13:25.850
The path to becoming alpha.

183
00:13:25.933 --> 00:13:27.852
It's not uncommon
for organizations like this

184
00:13:27.935 --> 00:13:29.854
to isolate people
from their loved ones.

185
00:13:29.937 --> 00:13:32.273
They find an emotional wedge.
they drive it in.

186
00:13:32.356 --> 00:13:34.901
Once they do that.
they've got total control.

187
00:13:34.984 --> 00:13:36.402
{\an8}Can you get him out?

188
00:13:36.485 --> 00:13:39.780
{\an8}Aside from forcibly removing him.
if Jackson doesn't wanna leave.

189
00:13:39.864 --> 00:13:41.282
{\an8}there's really nothing I can do.

190
00:13:41.365 --> 00:13:42.992
{\an8}All we're asking is that you try.

191
00:13:44.368 --> 00:13:46.829
{\an8}You don't strike me as a man
to give up so easily.

192
00:13:48.581 --> 00:13:49.749
{\an8}No. sir. I'm not.

193
00:14:03.137 --> 00:14:04.639
{\an8}[cell phone ringing]

194
00:14:06.265 --> 00:14:07.308
{\an8}<i>-Hey.</i>
- Hey. guys.

195
00:14:07.391 --> 00:14:09.227
{\an8}I need to know all the info you can find

196
00:14:09.310 --> 00:14:11.479
{\an8}about an organization
called Positive Light.

197
00:14:11.562 --> 00:14:13.731
{\an8}<i>They've got a headquarters</i>
<i>outside of Missoula.</i>

198
00:14:13.814 --> 00:14:16.525
{\an8}I'm headed there tomorrow.
I need to know what I'm walking into.

199
00:14:16.609 --> 00:14:18.486
{\an8}-We'll get into it.
<i>- I'll be moving fast.</i>

200
00:14:18.569 --> 00:14:21.155
{\an8}They know I'm looking for Jackson.
They'll be ready for me.

201
00:14:25.159 --> 00:14:26.535
{\an8}[bird cawing]

202
00:14:58.609 --> 00:15:00.486
{\an8}Do you think we can do that tomorrow?

203
00:15:01.529 --> 00:15:02.655
{\an8}Thank you. You can go.

204
00:15:03.531 --> 00:15:05.241
{\an8}Where's Jackson Cheong?

205
00:15:05.324 --> 00:15:09.453
{\an8}Mr. Shaw. I had a feeling
we'd be seeing you again.

206
00:15:09.870 --> 00:15:10.955
Where is he?

207
00:15:11.038 --> 00:15:13.291
There's no need for the tough-guy pose.

208
00:15:13.374 --> 00:15:16.002
Jackson's not being kept here
against his will.

209
00:15:16.085 --> 00:15:18.045
Then he can tell me that himself.

210
00:15:19.255 --> 00:15:22.341
Colter... May I call you Colter?

211
00:15:23.718 --> 00:15:24.886
Jackson's happy here.

212
00:15:25.553 --> 00:15:27.013
He's found his place with us.

213
00:15:27.638 --> 00:15:30.892
and we've really come to depend
on his financial guidance.

214
00:15:31.684 --> 00:15:34.687
Great. Where is he?

215
00:15:35.438 --> 00:15:37.732
Unfortunately.
he's in a session with Seth.

216
00:15:39.483 --> 00:15:40.860
I figured he might be.

217
00:15:40.943 --> 00:15:42.612
Perhaps you'd like to meet Seth.

218
00:15:43.195 --> 00:15:45.114
I'd really like to see Jackson.

219
00:15:46.908 --> 00:15:49.243
I'm afraid
that's not going to be possible

220
00:15:49.327 --> 00:15:51.120
unless you meet with Seth first.

221
00:15:57.209 --> 00:15:58.544
Okay.

222
00:16:04.842 --> 00:16:06.427
- Are you ready?
- [knocking on door]

223
00:16:09.555 --> 00:16:11.891
Seth. this is Colter Shaw.

224
00:16:11.974 --> 00:16:13.351
Mr. Shaw.

225
00:16:17.271 --> 00:16:18.648
It's good to see you again.

226
00:16:19.941 --> 00:16:21.734
I'm here to see Jackson Cheong.

227
00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:23.611
Rebecca explained.

228
00:16:24.862 --> 00:16:26.489
But I can't allow that to happen

229
00:16:26.572 --> 00:16:29.575
until we've had a chance to talk
and take your measure.

230
00:16:29.659 --> 00:16:31.285
I'm not sure what we'd talk about.

231
00:16:31.786 --> 00:16:34.747
[Seth] Why don't we start
with something simple?

232
00:16:34.830 --> 00:16:35.957
Tell me about yourself.

233
00:16:37.083 --> 00:16:39.877
I like pina coladas.
getting caught in the rain.

234
00:16:39.961 --> 00:16:42.797
Mr. Shaw. I'd prefer
if we didn't waste each other's time.

235
00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:47.093
We already know a lot about you.
who you work with. all sorts of things.

236
00:16:47.176 --> 00:16:49.887
So you got a peek at my ID
and you did some googling.

237
00:16:50.846 --> 00:16:52.515
I won't be intimidated like that.

238
00:16:53.849 --> 00:16:55.518
I'm not trying to intimidate you.

239
00:16:56.644 --> 00:16:57.979
I'm not a violent man.

240
00:16:58.729 --> 00:17:00.356
There are all types of violence.

241
00:17:01.148 --> 00:17:02.275
I suppose that's true.

242
00:17:03.276 --> 00:17:04.277
Tell me.

243
00:17:06.279 --> 00:17:08.197
what sort of man was your father?

244
00:17:11.617 --> 00:17:13.244
I'm not here to talk about that.

245
00:17:13.869 --> 00:17:15.746
It's okay to talk about the past.

246
00:17:15.830 --> 00:17:17.290
It's part of what we do here.

247
00:17:17.999 --> 00:17:20.126
You blackmail your members
with their secrets?

248
00:17:20.918 --> 00:17:22.044
Truth.

249
00:17:22.795 --> 00:17:25.172
We did look you up. Your family. too.

250
00:17:26.632 --> 00:17:28.259
Can't be too careful these days.

251
00:17:28.885 --> 00:17:31.846
and information. it's there
if you know where to look.

252
00:17:35.766 --> 00:17:36.851
Your father...

253
00:17:38.978 --> 00:17:40.229
Quite an impressive man.

254
00:17:41.355 --> 00:17:43.900
A scientist. then activist.

255
00:17:46.110 --> 00:17:47.278
Then he fell.

256
00:17:48.195 --> 00:17:50.865
Cliff near your family homestead.
if I'm not mistaken.

257
00:17:51.657 --> 00:17:52.742
An accident.

258
00:17:53.910 --> 00:17:55.953
At least that's what the newspaper said.

259
00:17:57.622 --> 00:17:59.749
But your eyes tell me
something different.

260
00:18:01.584 --> 00:18:02.585
Maybe he jumped?

261
00:18:04.879 --> 00:18:05.922
Or was pushed?

262
00:18:07.381 --> 00:18:10.551
Is the not knowing the source
of all that pain you're carrying?

263
00:18:13.179 --> 00:18:16.474
Tell me how he came
to be fired from his job as professor.

264
00:18:18.142 --> 00:18:19.560
Google didn't tell you that?

265
00:18:20.728 --> 00:18:21.729
No.

266
00:18:22.980 --> 00:18:24.690
Oh. you don't know why. do you?

267
00:18:27.276 --> 00:18:29.320
So your mother keeps secrets from you.

268
00:18:30.738 --> 00:18:31.948
Interesting.

269
00:18:34.784 --> 00:18:36.160
I'd like to see Jackson.

270
00:18:36.244 --> 00:18:39.622
Tell me one truth about your father.
and I will let you see Jackson.

271
00:18:40.248 --> 00:18:41.332
It's that simple.

272
00:18:41.666 --> 00:18:43.417
He made me the man that I am.

273
00:18:44.085 --> 00:18:47.255
But it wasn't easy. was it.
growing up with a father like that?

274
00:18:47.338 --> 00:18:49.966
Prepared me for people like you
who like to play games.

275
00:18:50.049 --> 00:18:51.842
Your father liked to play games?

276
00:18:51.926 --> 00:18:54.095
Tell me what sort of games
he liked to play.

277
00:18:54.178 --> 00:18:57.139
My father didn't play games.
All was life or death with him.

278
00:18:57.723 --> 00:19:00.017
Preparing you
to live in this world perhaps.

279
00:19:00.101 --> 00:19:01.102
Perhaps.

280
00:19:03.187 --> 00:19:04.981
I'm sorry you had to endure that.

281
00:19:07.149 --> 00:19:09.819
But thank you for opening up to me.

282
00:19:10.653 --> 00:19:12.154
I know that wasn't easy.

283
00:19:12.238 --> 00:19:16.576
But it shows me that you might be
someone I can grow to trust.

284
00:19:17.702 --> 00:19:18.786
I don't think so.

285
00:19:23.749 --> 00:19:26.168
You bring that near me.
I'll shove it down your throat.

286
00:19:31.048 --> 00:19:34.427
You get a burn when you witness
and hold another person's secrets.

287
00:19:44.478 --> 00:19:47.648
It is an honor to share one of yours.
Colter Shaw.

288
00:19:51.694 --> 00:19:53.946
Jackson will be waiting for you
in the garden.

289
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.668
Are you sure this is a good idea?

290
00:20:08.711 --> 00:20:09.837
Jackson's one of ours.

291
00:20:11.964 --> 00:20:13.925
Let Mr. Shaw talk to him and he'll see.

292
00:20:14.425 --> 00:20:16.052
And if he does cause trouble?

293
00:20:16.135 --> 00:20:18.221
Mr. Shaw has
a very dangerous profession.

294
00:20:21.432 --> 00:20:22.558
Accidents happen.

295
00:20:29.317 --> 00:20:31.569
- [Colter] <i>Yeah.</i>
- Are you in a good place to talk?

296
00:20:31.652 --> 00:20:33.154
Not really. You talk.
I'll listen.

297
00:20:33.237 --> 00:20:34.780
Is that not how we do it?

298
00:20:34.864 --> 00:20:37.283
I'm serious. Bobby.
You gotta be careful on this one.

299
00:20:37.366 --> 00:20:39.368
Copy that. Always am.

300
00:20:39.452 --> 00:20:42.622
So. yeah. Teddi and Velma called.
gave me the scoop.

301
00:20:42.705 --> 00:20:45.166
<i>- Positive Light. Super weird.</i>
- Mmm-hmm.

302
00:20:45.249 --> 00:20:47.043
There's nothing negative
about them online.

303
00:20:47.126 --> 00:20:50.588
No articles. no message boards.
<i>Nada.</i> man.

304
00:20:50.671 --> 00:20:51.714
Doesn't seem right.

305
00:20:51.797 --> 00:20:54.800
<i>Yeah. Hell. no. it ain't.
I started digging into archives.</i>

306
00:20:54.884 --> 00:20:58.095
Mostly dead links. Stuff that's been
completely wiped from the Internet.

307
00:20:58.179 --> 00:21:01.349
<i>and I found a bunch of lawsuits.
mostly civil cases.</i>

308
00:21:01.432 --> 00:21:03.893
<i>that either have been settled
or abruptly dropped.</i>

309
00:21:03.976 --> 00:21:05.353
Like Rebecca's charges?

310
00:21:05.811 --> 00:21:10.107
Mmm-hmm. A bunch of the cases called for
a David Grassley as a witness.

311
00:21:10.191 --> 00:21:12.276
<i>He and his wife. Jana.
were both members.</i>

312
00:21:12.360 --> 00:21:15.863
It looks like David prepared the
Positive Lights' financial statements.

313
00:21:15.947 --> 00:21:17.990
and he was a signer
on all their accounts.

314
00:21:18.074 --> 00:21:19.492
You got an address for me?

315
00:21:19.575 --> 00:21:22.578
Well. that's the thing.
David Grassley's dead.

316
00:21:23.246 --> 00:21:24.539
When. how?

317
00:21:24.622 --> 00:21:25.706
Hit-and-run.

318
00:21:25.957 --> 00:21:27.708
<i>Cops never found the driver.</i>

319
00:21:27.792 --> 00:21:29.168
The wife made a big stink

320
00:21:29.252 --> 00:21:32.547
about how the cops were all botching
the investigation on purpose.

321
00:21:32.630 --> 00:21:33.756
but she's gone quiet.

322
00:21:33.840 --> 00:21:35.800
<i>Packed up and moved
to southern Wyoming.</i>

323
00:21:35.883 --> 00:21:38.678
If she's afraid to talk.
we need to send someone there in person

324
00:21:38.761 --> 00:21:40.221
to make her feel comfortable.

325
00:21:40.304 --> 00:21:42.014
- Where exactly in Wyoming?
<i>- Cheyenne.</i>

326
00:21:42.098 --> 00:21:44.433
It's less than two hours from Denver.
Do you mind...

327
00:21:44.517 --> 00:21:46.894
Talking to Velma and Teddi?
I'm on it.

328
00:21:52.275 --> 00:21:56.404
Jackson. I'm Colter Shaw.
Someplace we could talk in private?

329
00:21:57.321 --> 00:21:58.447
I'm on gardening duty.

330
00:22:00.616 --> 00:22:02.743
But if you wanna talk. you can help me.

331
00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:10.001
I'm not coming home.

332
00:22:11.043 --> 00:22:12.837
My parents should know that by now.

333
00:22:13.045 --> 00:22:15.673
Your parents didn't even
know where you were until last night.

334
00:22:15.756 --> 00:22:17.133
You can tell them I'm fine.

335
00:22:18.176 --> 00:22:19.927
I'm better than fine. I'm happy.

336
00:22:20.261 --> 00:22:21.971
Great. Why don't you tell them yourself?

337
00:22:23.347 --> 00:22:27.643
Seth says I'm at a very a delicate stage
of my development.

338
00:22:28.978 --> 00:22:30.730
I don't think that's a good idea.

339
00:22:39.614 --> 00:22:43.701
When the soil is hard like that.
you just start shallow. right?

340
00:22:44.785 --> 00:22:47.455
And then you can always
go deeper on your second pass.

341
00:22:47.914 --> 00:22:48.998
Makes sense?

342
00:22:49.540 --> 00:22:51.250
- You a gardener. too?
- Kinda.

343
00:22:51.334 --> 00:22:54.212
Yeah. My dad taught me.
He believed in self-sufficiency.

344
00:22:55.546 --> 00:22:59.008
You gotta be able to feed yourself.
Growing own food was part of that.

345
00:22:59.759 --> 00:23:01.677
Seth wants us to be
self-sufficient. too.

346
00:23:02.220 --> 00:23:03.804
To know our own strength.

347
00:23:05.640 --> 00:23:07.850
My parents spent
their whole lives hovering.

348
00:23:09.310 --> 00:23:10.353
If it were up to them.

349
00:23:10.436 --> 00:23:12.563
I'd still be sleeping
in my childhood bedroom.

350
00:23:14.148 --> 00:23:15.191
Huh.

351
00:23:16.442 --> 00:23:19.695
What about all these cameras. though?
Isn't that "hovering"?

352
00:23:20.821 --> 00:23:23.866
The people in my stage
need more support to stay on the path.

353
00:23:24.408 --> 00:23:26.494
You've got people
who check on you. right?

354
00:23:27.328 --> 00:23:28.412
Seth tell you that?

355
00:23:28.496 --> 00:23:31.749
Seth trusts me
with important information.

356
00:23:31.832 --> 00:23:33.584
Financial information. Is that right?

357
00:23:33.668 --> 00:23:35.670
I'm not just some numbers-cruncher.

358
00:23:36.337 --> 00:23:39.465
Seth makes me feel
like I can do anything I put my mind to.

359
00:23:39.549 --> 00:23:41.884
Does that include
walking out the door right now?

360
00:23:43.511 --> 00:23:44.887
I'm not gonna do that.

361
00:23:48.099 --> 00:23:50.434
Why don't you give it a try?

362
00:23:52.895 --> 00:23:55.940
Shallow. then deep.
There you go. Easier?

363
00:23:57.817 --> 00:23:59.443
Your dad knew what he was doing.

364
00:23:59.986 --> 00:24:02.613
He knew his way around the outdoors.
that's for sure.

365
00:24:03.948 --> 00:24:06.701
He could be very charming.
A lot of charisma.

366
00:24:09.287 --> 00:24:12.373
I remember as a kid.
when he would look at me.

367
00:24:12.456 --> 00:24:16.878
sometimes it felt like he was
just looking right into me.

368
00:24:20.047 --> 00:24:21.090
He sounds like Seth.

369
00:24:22.425 --> 00:24:23.718
When Seth looks at you.

370
00:24:24.218 --> 00:24:25.511
How does it make you feel?

371
00:24:27.471 --> 00:24:28.556
Like I'm free.

372
00:24:30.516 --> 00:24:33.978
Free of all the things
that held me back.

373
00:24:39.609 --> 00:24:41.235
It sure wasn't like that with my dad.

374
00:24:42.445 --> 00:24:43.613
He could be mean.

375
00:24:44.614 --> 00:24:45.698
Impossible to please.

376
00:24:47.617 --> 00:24:51.370
I kept trying.
I tried until the day he died.

377
00:24:52.830 --> 00:24:54.123
Does that sound familiar?

378
00:24:55.416 --> 00:24:56.417
Seth ever mean?

379
00:24:57.126 --> 00:24:59.420
Jackson? How about Rebecca?
Is she ever mean?

380
00:25:03.758 --> 00:25:05.468
They only want what's best for me.

381
00:25:16.938 --> 00:25:19.815
Yeah. Listen. I gotta go.

382
00:25:21.108 --> 00:25:22.109
My number. Okay?

383
00:25:24.862 --> 00:25:27.281
Give me a call.
Reach out if you ever wanna talk.

384
00:25:29.242 --> 00:25:30.409
You stay or go.

385
00:25:30.826 --> 00:25:32.620
you decide what's best for you.

386
00:25:34.205 --> 00:25:35.289
Why do you care?

387
00:25:37.375 --> 00:25:38.543
You don't even know me.

388
00:25:39.585 --> 00:25:40.628
I don't know you?

389
00:25:42.463 --> 00:25:43.673
I used to be you.

390
00:25:49.679 --> 00:25:52.181
All right. nice chatting with you.
Good luck.

391
00:25:53.224 --> 00:25:55.852
When can we make time
for another session. Mr. Shaw?

392
00:25:55.935 --> 00:25:58.855
- We're just getting started.
- Yep. I'll see myself out.

393
00:26:09.283 --> 00:26:10.493
[phone vibrates]

394
00:27:03.629 --> 00:27:05.214
I know why you're here. Colter.

395
00:27:06.048 --> 00:27:07.133
Where's Jackson?

396
00:27:07.216 --> 00:27:09.760
He's on a healing retreat.
You won't find him.

397
00:27:13.723 --> 00:27:15.683
You kidnapped him
because he reached out to me?

398
00:27:15.766 --> 00:27:17.727
No. He went voluntarily.

399
00:27:17.810 --> 00:27:22.064
He gave me your number voluntarily. too.
I'm the one who texted you.

400
00:27:22.148 --> 00:27:25.526
I know it's hard to believe
because you're naturally suspicious.

401
00:27:25.610 --> 00:27:26.903
But I don't blame you.

402
00:27:26.986 --> 00:27:29.530
Who wouldn't be
after your difficult childhood?

403
00:27:30.281 --> 00:27:32.533
You live on the road
trying to run away from it.

404
00:27:32.617 --> 00:27:36.370
but you can never really
leave it all behind. can you. Colter?

405
00:27:38.247 --> 00:27:39.332
Where'd you take him?

406
00:27:40.708 --> 00:27:42.460
I won't let you pull him back down.

407
00:27:43.377 --> 00:27:46.255
But the door to a new life
is always open to you.

408
00:27:46.339 --> 00:27:49.592
But should you choose a different path.

409
00:27:50.718 --> 00:27:53.262
please know that we defend
our own. Colter.

410
00:27:53.846 --> 00:27:55.598
We protect them from the wolves

411
00:27:55.681 --> 00:27:58.768
and the darkness that you're trying
to bring to Jackson's life.

412
00:27:59.685 --> 00:28:00.686
That a threat?

413
00:28:00.770 --> 00:28:02.939
Oh. I think you know
exactly what I mean.

414
00:28:26.671 --> 00:28:28.047
You can go.

415
00:28:31.300 --> 00:28:33.886
But if it were up to me.
you'll be gone permanently.

416
00:28:33.970 --> 00:28:37.098
Well. lucky for me
you're not in charge. are you?

417
00:28:42.395 --> 00:28:43.396
Do you have Jackson?

418
00:28:43.479 --> 00:28:46.149
[Colter] <i>They got wind of our meet</i>
<i>and got him before I arrived.</i>

419
00:28:46.232 --> 00:28:48.192
He's valuable to them.
He's the new accountant.

420
00:28:48.276 --> 00:28:49.986
They won't let him go
without a fight.

421
00:28:50.069 --> 00:28:51.362
Just like David Grassley.

422
00:28:51.445 --> 00:28:53.489
We just met with his widow Jana.

423
00:28:53.573 --> 00:28:55.992
<i>She said David found out
Seth and Rebecca</i>

424
00:28:56.075 --> 00:28:58.578
<i>were draining
the bank accounts of their followers.</i>

425
00:28:58.661 --> 00:29:01.414
and when he tried to leave.
they killed him.

426
00:29:01.497 --> 00:29:04.333
Jana told us that Seth has photos
of the hit-and-run

427
00:29:04.417 --> 00:29:05.501
that killed her husband.

428
00:29:05.585 --> 00:29:08.171
These people film everything.
They filmed that.

429
00:29:08.254 --> 00:29:11.757
Seth has physical photos
of a murder? Where?

430
00:29:11.841 --> 00:29:14.010
Jana said that the photos
were at Seth's office.

431
00:29:14.093 --> 00:29:15.720
It's some instructional center.

432
00:29:15.803 --> 00:29:18.389
<i>They are so paranoid about
getting hacked.</i>

433
00:29:18.473 --> 00:29:22.018
that he keeps the files of everyone
he's ever met at that office.

434
00:29:22.101 --> 00:29:24.270
Jana say where this
instructional center is?

435
00:29:24.353 --> 00:29:26.022
<i>No. they blindfolded her on the way.</i>

436
00:29:26.105 --> 00:29:28.191
She wasn't even sure
what direction it was in.

437
00:29:28.274 --> 00:29:29.567
We're sure she's credible?

438
00:29:29.650 --> 00:29:32.570
She was heartbroken. Colter.
and she was terrified.

439
00:29:32.653 --> 00:29:34.489
<i>She's seen the photos herself.</i>

440
00:29:34.572 --> 00:29:36.782
Seth showed her the photos
to keep her quiet.

441
00:29:36.866 --> 00:29:38.534
Yeah. we both believed her.

442
00:29:42.872 --> 00:29:44.457
I gotta go. I'm being followed.

443
00:30:06.729 --> 00:30:07.772
[horn honks]

444
00:30:41.389 --> 00:30:43.933
I couldn't help but notice
you're following me.

445
00:30:44.016 --> 00:30:45.101
Positive Light send you?

446
00:30:46.227 --> 00:30:47.645
Why don't I save you the trouble?

447
00:30:47.728 --> 00:30:50.356
Why don't you take me
to the instructional facility

448
00:30:50.439 --> 00:30:51.524
where Seth's office is?

449
00:31:16.841 --> 00:31:18.801
- [grunts]
- Thanks for the lift.

450
00:32:22.201 --> 00:32:24.453
Teddi. I found photos
of that dashcam video

451
00:32:24.536 --> 00:32:27.581
that show the hit-and-run of
that accountant. David Grassley.

452
00:32:27.664 --> 00:32:32.169
I'm sending you a pin right now.
you should have it.

453
00:32:33.086 --> 00:32:34.588
Send the cops to the location.

454
00:33:10.749 --> 00:33:14.044
<i>There were arrests.
Fraud. bad checks...</i>

455
00:34:12.436 --> 00:34:13.479
Jackson.

456
00:34:18.817 --> 00:34:21.236
We gotta get you out of here.
These people are dangerous.

457
00:34:21.320 --> 00:34:22.529
Rebecca told me you'd come.

458
00:34:22.613 --> 00:34:25.282
Yeah. Name David Grassley
mean anything to you?

459
00:34:25.365 --> 00:34:27.951
He was the accountant
for Positive Light before you.

460
00:34:30.412 --> 00:34:31.413
Look at that.

461
00:34:31.497 --> 00:34:32.498
What is this?

462
00:34:33.165 --> 00:34:34.166
They killed him.

463
00:34:34.958 --> 00:34:37.211
They killed him
when he tried to leave Positive Light.

464
00:34:37.294 --> 00:34:39.880
It was a hit-and-run.
The cops couldn't figure out who did it.

465
00:34:40.005 --> 00:34:42.257
Somehow. Seth and Rebecca
have all the dashcam footage.

466
00:34:42.341 --> 00:34:44.593
- Why do you suppose that is?
- I don't know.

467
00:34:44.676 --> 00:34:45.677
This is what they do.

468
00:34:46.512 --> 00:34:48.514
This is what Seth
and Rebecca Pendergast

469
00:34:48.597 --> 00:34:50.724
do to their followers
when they step out of line.

470
00:34:50.808 --> 00:34:52.601
I don't know a Rebecca Pendergast.

471
00:34:52.684 --> 00:34:53.811
You do. Look.

472
00:34:54.645 --> 00:34:57.815
It's Rebecca.
Look. she made a video. here.

473
00:34:59.191 --> 00:35:00.192
Yeah.

474
00:35:00.651 --> 00:35:02.694
I guess. to prove her loyalty to Seth.

475
00:35:04.738 --> 00:35:06.698
- They make all of us testify.
- Yeah?

476
00:35:08.492 --> 00:35:09.576
Watch.

477
00:35:11.370 --> 00:35:12.621
[Rebecca] <i>There were arrests.</i>

478
00:35:14.748 --> 00:35:15.833
<i>Fraud. bad checks.</i>

479
00:35:16.708 --> 00:35:20.462
<i>My father disowned me
after the second one.</i>

480
00:35:21.213 --> 00:35:23.465
<i>He told everyone he never had children.</i>

481
00:35:25.259 --> 00:35:27.302
Jackson. we gotta go.

482
00:35:29.221 --> 00:35:31.181
She told me her father
committed suicide.

483
00:35:33.767 --> 00:35:35.269
I got my first burn because

484
00:35:36.395 --> 00:35:39.523
she said she was sharing
a secret with me.

485
00:35:40.607 --> 00:35:42.234
I told you to stay away. Colter.

486
00:35:44.403 --> 00:35:45.946
You should have listened to me.

487
00:35:47.030 --> 00:35:50.534
Step away from him.
Security's on its way.

488
00:35:51.660 --> 00:35:52.828
So are the police.

489
00:35:52.911 --> 00:35:56.123
Great. It saves us the trouble
of calling them ourselves.

490
